article.description: — AJ Wilson had 22 points and 10 rebounds as George Mason narrowly beat VMI 68-66 on Monday.
article.headline: Wilson scores 22 to lead George Mason over VMI 68-66
article.linkText: Wilson scores 22 to lead George Mason over VMI 68-66
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- — AJ Wilson had 22 points and 10 rebounds as George Mason narrowly beat VMI 68-66 on Monday. Xavier Johnson made two free throws with four seconds left to give George Mason a 68-63 lead. Tyler Kolek had 11 points and five steals for George Mason (3-1). Greg Parham had 19 points for the Keydets (5-4). Kamdyn Curfman added 14 points and Jake Stephens had 14 points, 10 rebounds and four assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
